# Quick Make Commands Reference

## Essential Commands
make run          # Start the application
make dev          # Start with hot reload (recommended for development)
make test         # Run all tests
make build        # Build the project

## Database Commands
make migrate      # Apply database migrations
make migration    # Create new migration (add NAME=YourMigrationName)
make db-drop      # Drop the database

## Maintenance Commands
make clean        # Clean build artifacts
make restore      # Restore NuGet packages
make format       # Format code

## Testing Commands
make test         # Run all tests
make test-watch   # Run tests in watch mode
make test-coverage # Run tests with code coverage

## Help
make help         # Show all available commands

## First Time Setup
1. Install make: winget install GnuWin32.Make
2. Restart terminal
3. Run: make restore
4. Run: make migrate
5. Run: make dev
